author: Jordan Smith
title: Caitlyn Jenner Plans 2017 Return
text:
Caitlyn Jenner is planning a comeback in 2017 that could include a nude photo shoot.
The Olympic medal winner is reportedly seeking to bounce back after 2016, when her television show “I am Cait was cancelled,” according to Fox News.
Jenner is allegedly hoping to draw inspiration from Kim Kardashian.
“Cait wants to do something along the lines of what Kim did on the cover of Paper magazine. No one has worked harder than Cait to get the body she wants and naturally she wants to show it off,” a source said, Fox reported.
Jenner received considerable media coverage during 2015 when she underwent gender transition.
Jenner made an appearance at the Gold Meets Golden event in Los Angeles Jan. 6 alongside actress Nicole Kidman. The event raises awareness of sports-related causes.
This year, it was also being held to build support for the city’s bid to host the 2024 Olympic and Paralympic games.
Jenner, dressed in black, posed for a picture with former gymnast Nadia Komaneci, Daily Mail reported.
She has also been making headlines for her newly-released collection of MAC products. The response to MAC’s Caitlyn Jenner Collection was mixed, with a large number of negative comments, according to Metro.
Some included, “No,” “Eww,” “Won’t be buying that” and”Put off your product forever,” Metro reported.
